    <abstract>
      <t>This document specifies a protocol that installs, updates, and
   deletes Trusted Applications (TAs) in a device with a Trusted
   Execution Environment (TEE).  Due to its function it is called
   "Trusted Execution Environment Provisioning (TEEP) Protocol", which
   provides interoperability for mantaining the lifecycle of TAs.</t>
    </abstract>
